			    <h2>Research Topics </h2>
			    <div class="inner">
					I am currently persuing my doctoral degree in the department of <a href="http://www.eng.uci.edu/dept/eecs">EECS</a>,
					 Henry Samueli School of Engineering. I am expecting my defence on <b>March, 2014</b>. My research is constantly supported
					 by the EECS department fellowships and research assistantships. My adivisor is Prof. 
					 Ozdal Boyraz. My research topics includes 
					<ul>
						<li>Silicon waveguide technology, including silicon waveguide on silica/sapphire, silicon nitride waveguide</li>
						<li>Planer reflective devices based on plasmonics, e.g. flat reflectors, flat polarization converters</li>
						<li>Silicon based nonlinear optics: four-wave-mixing parametric process and wavelength conversion</li>
						<li>Mid infrared silicon photonics: mid-IR signal detection and sensing</li>
						<li>Gas sensing and detection: evanescent field sensor based on silicon-on-sapphire waveguides</li>
						<li>Microwave photonics: ultrafast optical ADC, arbitrary waveform generation, 3D imaging system</li>
						<li>Left-handed metamaterial in microwave and optical frequency</li>
						<li>Pattern recognition, machine learning, support vector machines (SVM)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
